Rating: 4
LOVED THIS! I actually cooked it in my slow cooker without marinating. Put all the ingredients right in the crock for 4-5 hours on low, and it was delicious! Shredded up excellently. The only think I will do differently next time (and there will be a next time!) is not to salt. The flavors in a crock pot become very concentrated, which I loved for the other seasonings, but felt it was a little too salty. Next time I will cook the same, but salt to taste when serving. I made this to accompany the black bean cakes, but will be eating the leftovers stand-alone!

