I doubled the amount of this marinade (not the jalapenos, though) for two pounds of pork tenderloin. The results were amazing. I think we're using this as a dinner during the Christmas holidays - it was that good and that easy.

Rating: 4
Great recipe! If you love flavorful dishes, this jerk sauce is excellent - don't be afraid of using the hot peppers, even WITH the seeds as the pork will absorb the flavors and provide for a terrific dish. I prefer to use pork shoulder, and about 4-5 lbs of it. This sauce recipe, doubled, will more than do the trick. I've made this many times and it is an amazing winner among friends.

Rating: 4
I made this rub with pork chops, topped it with pineapple salsa, and served it with sweet potato fries. I also mixed a little pineapple juice with sour cream and put a drop of that on top...all I can say is YUMMY! My husband who thinks that pineapples served with meat should be illegal even loved it...and he took the left overs to work with him for lunch (always a sign of success). It's so easy and tasty...you've gotta try it!

