Rating: 3
YUM! This was great, and as close to real jerk as I have had outside of Jamaica. We used just 2 jalapenos, it was spicy enough for us. I thought shredding the pork was difficult,it was easier when the pork was sliced into slices thinner than the 1-inch-thickness recommended by the recipe.

Rating: 3
This was very easy and really delicious. I doubled the amount of lime juice and the amount of soy sauce, plus I upped the nutmeg a bit - came out great. I ended up marinating it for probably 24 hours, which was fine. Instead of coupling this recipe with the one for red pepper mayo and bean cakes, I just used the meat in a sandwich with some roasted red peppers on top - the sweetness of the red pepper and the spiciness of the meat are wonderfully complentary - I will definitly try the mayo/bean cake portion of the recipe soon.

